<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4"><b><a href="../2008-1/669/669_02_Fiddling.shtml">Fiddling while the economy burns</a></b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">John McCain is proposing warmed-over supply-side economics--and there's less to the Democrats' criticisms of business than meets the eye.<p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4"><b><a href="../2008-1/667/667_03_Wright.shtml">The making of a scapegoat</a></b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">If Rev. Jeremiah Wright used angry rhetoric, perhaps it's because there's still a lot in American society to be angry about.<p>

